## How the data was collected?
The data was collected by me from [pexels](pexels.com) using the following [library](https://github.com/olegkhomenko/pexels-downloader). All images are of the original size(the original size that was available on the website) without any compression.

## What is in it?
The dataset contains images in sub-directories. Each sub-directory is named after the type of image that it holds. For example, the sub-directory "trains" contains images of trains. 

## What can this be used for?
I collected this data to train a model for removing motion blur from images but this data can be used for a wide variety of tasks like super-resolution, multi-label classification etc.

## Whom to thank for?
The images in this data are original work of their creators and are available on [pexels](pexels.com). These images can therefore be used for free as per the license requirement mentioned in pexels.com.
